{"title_page": "1st Division (North Korea)", "text_new": "The '''1st Infantry Division''' is a military formation of the [[Korean People's Army]].{{infobox military unit\n| unit_name = Guards 1st Infantry Division\n| image = KPA Guards Badge.svg\n| image_size = 50px\n| caption = Guards badge\n| dates = 1948-present\n| country = {{Flagicon|North Korea}} [[North Korea]]\n| allegiance = [[File:Flag of the Korean People's Army Ground Force.svg|20px]] [[Korean People's Army]]\n| branch = [[Korean People's Army Ground Force]]\n| type = [[Infantry division]]\n| role = \n| size = [[Division (military)|Division]]\n| command_structure = \n| garrison = [[Kosong County]], [[Kangwon Province (North Korea)|Kangwon Province]]\n| garrison_label = \n| nickname = \n| patron = \n| motto = \n| colors = \n| colors_label = \n| march = \n| mascot = \n| equipment = \n| equipment_label = \n| battles = [[Korean War]]\n| anniversaries = \n| decorations = Guards badge\n| battle_honours = \n| disbanded = \n| notable_commanders = \n}}It was part of the North Korean advance from [[Seoul]] to [[Taejon]].\n\nThe division fought in the [[Battle of Pusan Perimeter]].<ref>{{cite book|url=http://www.history.army.mil/brochures/KW-Outbreak/outbreak.htm|title=The Korean War: The Outbreak|publisher=[[United States Army Center of Military History]]|first=William J.|last=Webb|id=CMH Pub 19-6}}</ref>\n\nThe intelligence section of [[Far East Command (United States)|U.S Far East Command]] headquarters listed the divisions order of battle as a 31 July 1952 as follows:<ref>{{cite book|title=History of the North Korean Army|date=31 July 1952|publisher=Headquarters, Far East Command. Intelligence Section|pages=141}}</ref>\n*2nd Regiment\n*3rd Regiment\n*14th Regiment\n*Artillery Regiment\n\nThis same report listed the 1st Division as being in III Corps Reserve at the same time period.<ref>{{cite book|title=History of the North Korean Army|date=31 July 1952|publisher=Headquarters, Far East Command. Intelligence Section|pages=75}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Military units and formations of North Korea in the Korean War|InfDiv0001]]\n[[Category:Infantry divisions of North Korea|InfDiv0001NK]]\n\n\n{{Mil-unit-stub}}\n{{NorthKorea-mil-stub}}\n", "text_old": "The '''1st Infantry Division''' is a military formation of the [[Korean People's Army]].{{infobox military unit\n| unit_name = Guards 1st Infantry Division\n| image = KPA Guards Badge.svg\n| image_size = 50px\n| caption = Guards badge\n| dates = 1948-present\n| country = {{Flagicon|North Korea}} [[North Korea]]\n| allegiance = [[File:Flag of the Korean People's Army Ground Force.svg|20px]] [[Korean People's Army]]\n| branch = [[Korean People's Army Ground Force]]\n| type = [[Infantry division]]\n| role = \n| size = [[Division (military)|Division]]\n| command_structure = \n| garrison = [[Kosong County]], [[Kangwon Province (North Korea)|Kangwon Province]]]]\n| garrison_label = \n| nickname = \n| patron = \n| motto = \n| colors = \n| colors_label = \n| march = \n| mascot = \n| equipment = \n| equipment_label = \n| battles = [[Korean War]]\n| anniversaries = \n| decorations = Guards badge\n| battle_honours = \n| disbanded = \n| notable_commanders = \n}}It was part of the North Korean advance from [[Seoul]] to [[Taejon]].\n\nThe division fought in the [[Battle of Pusan Perimeter]].<ref>{{cite book|url=http://www.history.army.mil/brochures/KW-Outbreak/outbreak.htm|title=The Korean War: The Outbreak|publisher=[[United States Army Center of Military History]]|first=William J.|last=Webb|id=CMH Pub 19-6}}</ref>\n\nThe intelligence section of [[Far East Command (United States)|U.S Far East Command]] headquarters listed the divisions order of battle as a 31 July 1952 as follows:<ref>{{cite book|title=History of the North Korean Army|date=31 July 1952|publisher=Headquarters, Far East Command. Intelligence Section|pages=141}}</ref>\n*2nd Regiment\n*3rd Regiment\n*14th Regiment\n*Artillery Regiment\n\nThis same repo